🚨 LONG MONOLOGUE ALERT 🚨 !
My dear friends! First of all, HAPPY HOLIDAYS to all of you!!! Despite my Instagram/Facebook glam and fun, December wasn’t an easy month for me. I’m still fighting this new flu that has caught me on December 5th and has been torturing me ever since. As soon as I thought it got better, a medical emergency of a close friend took me to Mexico, and then I barely made it back home for Christmas…only to drop the next day with fever AGAIN 🤷🏼‍♀️. So, my point is:

I’ve been a really pathetic friend and colleague this past month and throughout the holidays. I didn’t send out the holiday cards to my friends and relatives, I was awful responding to texts and calls and even worse at reaching out to my people to check on them or to wish them Happy Hanukkah and Merry Christmas. I was in and out of social media and missed a lot of friends’ posts and news. 
I know it might have hurt people’s feelings, and I truly apologize for this. Just know that I love you all, I care about you all, and I can’t wait to get back to a 100% and hug all of the friends whom I miss like crazy.
Love you, love you, love you!!!
Yours, Sasha ❤️

Getting these ready (eventually) for adoption!
Okay, now that I know the kittens’ personalities, and also after having checked their genders, I gave some of them names. 
Introducing:

1. Captain Kirk (photo 1) - fearless boy and definitely a leader!

2. Spock (photo 3) - well, Vulcans don’t express any emotions, as we know, but this boy is totally the opposite. He is so emotional and playful, that we couldn’t resist…

3. Elly May (photo 2) - an adorable and mischievous girl who steals hearts left and right without even noticing!

Calico mama cat got her name in the shelter. Her name is Fina, and although she was feral, she is a total love bug. As well as another feral momma cat named Ila. This beautiful black kitty begs for love! She tenderly puts her paws on my legs when I’m sitting there with her, and looks adoringly in the eye. We slow blink a lot at each other, as well as with Fina (see the video).
We rescued the two mommas and their kittens from a shelter where they have been scheduled to be killed that day.

They all, as it turned out, were sick (we are in the middle of their treatment now).
Ila’s story is a very sad one. She had 8 newborns. But 2 died in the shelter before she was rescued. Then, within 24 hours after getting her out, we lost 4 more kittens. We really hoped we’d be able to save their lives, but they had been too sick…
Two remaining newborns rejected mama’s milk, and I started syringe-feeding them. We named them Darth Vader and Maul Skywalker (combination of two Star Wars characters). Their mom and I team worked really hard on saving them. Unfortunately, it was too late for Skywalker…

As of now, Ila has only one kitten left - Darth Vader (who turned out to be a girl). We are fighting for her life. But she is too weak and lethargic. No matter what we do, she doesn’t get better. If we lose Vader, Ila will be completely alone. Having lost her kids.  She loves attention, pets and play. She will need a very loving home. I can tell that she has a very loving trusting heart.

There is one more calico girl kitten I haven’t introduced yet, but I’m still working on her name. 
I’ll post a photo of Darth Vader in stories. Please pray for her!🙏🏻🐈‍⬛

And today, on September 27th, 2023 
I have become a Citizen of the United States of America 🇺🇸. 
Everyone who knows me, knows what a journey it had been. Dreams do come true. I am living mine. I’m proud of myself for having built my own fairytale in every area of my life. I’m endlessly grateful that America believed in me just like I’ve always believed in myself. 
🇺🇸🇺🇸🇺🇸
While waiting for the ceremony today, I’ve been thinking of ALL the people who made it possible by helping me and supporting me in many different ways from the very beginning. YOU ALL MADE IT HAPPEN, and I’m forever grateful. Just to name a few: @juliakostenevich , @ladanikolska , @armenway , @windypress , @julia__chayko , @racheldb24 , @honkytonkandi , @mr.antontabakov @evgenykerbel and family, @wnmforever , @the_jeniverse , @kimsilversteinphotography , @jonathank.armstrong, @mrs_yuri and my entire Carthay fam, @captaineso ,  @gtsikhiseli , @olgakallas , @stanislavcallas , @oandi_design and his entire family, @karinafadeeva, @sergche , @cherevko.k, and many more people who fought for me, supported me when I needed it the most, provided their shoulders to cry on when I was miserable, and showed me their kindness and the beauty of their hearts. I’m so grateful to you all and for you all. ❤️
I want to mention here a wonderful man, @shanekbartlett whose life tragically ended earlier this year. I still can’t process this loss, still in denial. Shane was an extraordinary human being. And he fought for me. Shane, thank you so much 🙏🏻🤍…

And of course, my EVERYTHINGS: my half @silkbaron ❤️ and his supportive, loving family, my sisters @katya_kerbel_art (@katyakerbel ) and @juju4itaet (@juju.kerbel ), my brother-in-law Hatem and the entire Kinawy family, my kiddos Erik, Hassan, Youssef, Sonya. Akyra and Toby, Mariam and Kira. My 13 cats. My chosen sisters and brothers: @therachellehenry , @iamricoanderson , @omicronsoldiero , @ashallenmurphy, Rob LaSardo, @ambercarlton9 , @etuni , @jabakhazalia , @bellakellyofficial , @theofficialwillb , @joeythedancer ,  @thedesibaldwin , @kaylaperkins , @realdiana87 and my entire @arykas_ybots_pr_mgt_firm family.
Thank you for being by my side❤️! 🇺🇸

Beautiful Celebration of the beautiful Life. 
Roz Wyman was a real trailblazer. She changed history in so many ways. She made the world a better place. She lived a life that could fit 5 lifetimes, at least. 
I’m honored to have been invited by Roz’es loved ones to celebrate her extraordinary life and legacy here, in her most favorite city in the world…💙🤍💙 

Among many dreams that she turned into reality, it was Roz’es idea to connect Los Angeles City Hall up to Grand Avenue through a park where all Angelenos could gather. And we gathered. With dear friends, and new acquaintances, with people whose lives Roz Wyman and her family touched…

This is my Holiday post 🌟🌟🌟!

HOME FOR CHRISTMAS… AND FOR EVER!!! I couldn’t be happier this Holiday season! My sweet foster kitty Akay has been adopted! From the moment he, Molly and David saw each other, it was clear that this is a true match! His new family, that includes two other cats, loves him so much, and he is thriving! 🐈‍⬛
All the way from a scared baby euth listed at Devore Shelter, to a happy kitten who’s getting ready for his first ever Christmas!🎄And he’s got a new name! He is Nicky now🥹❤️!!!
Thank you Molly and David, you are a dream family! ❤️
Thank you @thecatsmeowanimalrescue for your tireless, ongoing effort to rescue cats!🙏🏻
Thank you @networkingdevoresheltercats for letting the world know about kitties in dire need! Because of your posts, Joyce, I started fostering.
Happy Holidays, and may miracles happen in each and every life!!!🥹

A former combat vet, Milles Carpis (Robert LaSardo), with tours in Iraq is haunted by memories of the war and struggling with PTSD. He finds solace in Melissa Maddox (Lorelei Linklater), a free spirited new age hippie environmentalist. She quickly develops an affection for Milles during a chance encounter when he reveals a secret admiration for Charles Manson. Melissa immediately anoints Milles devotee to her psychedelic world with a similar secret regarding Manson. They embark on a journey together down the disruptive streets of Venice California searching for a place in the sun. Their romance is suddenly interrupted by an event that reshapes both of their lives forever. 
“American Trash”. Coming soon!
